shared_text:
ISU Extension Buena Vista County
April 15 at 3:38 PM ¬∑

Congratulations to the ISU Extension and Outreach - Buena Vista County Council members who were named the County Extension Council Distinguished Service winner! We want to congratulate the council on this distinguished honor. The recognition is a direct reflection of the commitment, dedication and innovation they have shown as an Extension Council. Thank you for your leadership and support of Iowa State University Extension and Outreach. Members of the ISU Extension and Outreach Council in Buena Vista County are: Paul Diehl, CJ Bean, Landon Sullivan, Miguel Negrete, Laura Sievers, Jan Worthan, Melanie Bloom, Salli Nichols and Roman De La Torre.

post_text:
All,

I received word tonight that Governor Reynolds is recommending no school for 4 weeks. Despite having many questions myself, we will follow that recommendation, effective immediately, which means there will be NO SCHOOL beginning tomorrow, March 16, 2020. We will update you with more when I get that information. We will get through this as a community and district, I wish I had more.

Jeff Dicks, Superintendent

Nurse Notes~
My whole life we have known that smoking is harmful and that there is not one good reason to smoke. So, why do so many teens start? Today we talked about the dangers of smoking (and vaping with the older students), and as I do every year, I've challenged students to decide now what their answer will be if they are ever pressured to smoke or vape!
~Nure Julie
